title: For Sale:  Weatherby Ultramark .340 Mag Left Hand w/Weatherby Supreme 3X9 Scope
postcontent:
Weatherby Ultramark .340 Magnum Left Hand with aluminum bedding block synthetic Tan Spiderweb Stock. Has 26" barrel with Weatherby Accu-Brake. Also has Weatherby Supreme 3X9 Scope. 

Rifle is in very good condition, scope has a few marks from years of hunting in the mountains of Montana and Alaska. Rifle has taken 3 Moose, 24 Elk, 17 Mule deer, 1 Grizzly and 9 Black bear. I purchased new from Weatherby custom shop in 1989 with accurizing and lapped lugs and long throat options for large grain bullets.  is originally came with the fancy european exhibition grade walnut stock but the recoil lug kept breaking loose when I would shoot 250gr bullets, so it was replaced with a custom medalist stock that is free floated and aluminum pillar and bedding block system. 

Rifle was freshened up (de-fouled, action tuned, and barrel checked) 2 years ago by Upper Missouri Trading Company in Creston, Nebraska (Weatherby's Midwest Service Center). It took its last Elk, October of 2012 in Montana. I am too broken to hunt but the rifle is not!

A set of reloading dies, bullets, brass, reloads go with the rifle. If you do your homework you will see that the .340 mag is one of the flattest trajectories out there. Only a 7" arc from muzzle to point of impact at 400yds with 165gr ammo.

A new Ultramark is $2500-$5500 depending on options. I will let this go for $1,000 or best offer.

The 884 features the pure fluorite crystal “PROMINAR” 88-mm objective lens, the Kowa TSN-884 offers simply unsurpassed light throughput for the brightest, aberration free images. Despite the huge lens, the durable magnesium frame helps limit the weight of the Kowa TSN-884 to less than 54 oz. Kowa’s inner focus system shortens the prism box on the TSN-884 scope, giving it a compact 13.5 inch length. The Kowa TSN-884 spotting scope features a dual focus system with separate knobs for coarse and fine focusing, an eyepiece locking mechanism, and a tripod mount that adapts to accommodate either a 1/4- or a 3/8-inch mounting screw. With its superb optics and Kowa’s special adapters, the TSN-884 makes a great digiscoping rig. The Kowa TSN-884 scope is completely waterproof and nitrogen-purged to be internally fog-proof. 

The Gitzo tripod features a 6X carbon fiber tube, made of a unique structure of 6 crossed layers that maximises rigidity, vibration absorption and lightweight performance. 6X tube has a high density structure made of top quality ultra-thin carbon fibers (7mm or 0.007 mm). Built-in Anti Leg Rotation is now a feature of the whole carbon fiber range. Tripod also has a Gitzo G1177M series 1 Center Ball Head.

From a review in Accurateshooter.com by Danny Reever: 
One of my tests included a Snellen Eye Chart, just like the one at your optometrist office. Instead of it hanging on a wall, I placed the Snellen Chart at 500 meters along with some previously-shot paper Ground Hog targets. Conditions were hazy and humid with moderate mirage. My Nightforce 12-42x56mm Benchrest riflescope set at 42X could read line 6 on the chart and I could distinguish only a few of the 6mm bullet holes. My Pentax PF100-ED set at 60X (to match the Kowa’s maximum power) was better. With the Pentax I could read line 7 on the chart and see more of the bullet holes. With the Kowa set at 60X, I could read line 8 on the chart and see all of the bullet holes on the white parts of the targets.. FYI, line 8 on the Snellen Chart defines 20-20 vision at 20 feet. Reading that at 500 meters (1641 feet) is pretty impressive!
